{"word":"H5631 - סָרִיס - çârîyç - saw-reece' - Chamberlain","slug":"H5631","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">סָרִיס</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>çârîyç"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>saw-reece'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Chamberlain"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05E1;&#x05E8;&#x05E1;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&#x05E1;&#x05E8;&#x05D9;&#x05E1; - sa&#x0302;r&#x0131;&#x0302;ys  sa&#x0302;ris</b> - <i>saw-reece', saw-reece'</i><p/>From an unused root meaning to <i>castrate</i>; a <i>eunuch</i>; by implication <i>valet</i> (especially of the female apartments), and thus a <i>minister</i> of state: - chamberlain, eunuch, officer. Compare <a href=\"#/H7249\">H7249</a>."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H5628\">H5628</a>, <a href=\"#/H5629\">H5629</a>, <a href=\"#/H5630\">H5630</a>, <a href=\"#/H5633\">H5633</a>, <a href=\"#/H5636\">H5636</a>"}]}